[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["S-amer africa default banner.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Bloemfontein"]}," (",{"type":"''","value":["Fountain of flowers"]},"), ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.bloemfontein.co.za\/"]},", is the judicial capital of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["South Africa"]]},". It is also the capital of the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Free State"],["Free State Province"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\nBloemfontein was founded in 1846 and now has a population of around half a million people.\n\nJ. R. R. Tolkien, author of ",{"type":"'''","value":["The Lord of the Rings"]}," was born in Bloemfontein in 1892.\n\nIn 1923, the African National Congress (ANC) political party was founded in Bloemfontein.\n\nToday, Bloemfontein is a compact city surrounded by sprawling suburbs.\n\nHappily, the city centre is safe to walk around during the day, but many of the city's activities are focused on the Waterfront and Mimosa malls and on the large sporting complex. Second Avenue, north of the Waterfront mall, has the majority of the city's bars and restaurants.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By plane"]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.airports.co.za Bloemfontein Airport"]}]}," ((",{"type":"{{","value":[["IATA"],["BFN"]]},")) is just outside the city and a number of flights to major South African cities take off from here, operated by South African Airways ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.flysaa.com"]}," and SA Airlink ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/flyairlink.com"]},". and Mango airlines ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/ww5.flymango.co.za"]}," fly to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Cape Town"]]},"\n\nSee ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Air travel in South Africa"]]}," for more information.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\nBloemfontein is a major rail junction in the middle of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["South Africa"]]},". From here, Spoornet ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.spoornet.co.za\/ShosholozaMeyl"]},"  operates regular trains to all points of the country : ",{"type":"'''","value":["south"]}," to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Cape Town"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Port Elizabeth"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["East London"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mthatha"]]},", ",{"type":"'''","value":["west"]}," to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kimberley (South Africa)"],["Kimberley"]]},", ",{"type":"'''","value":["north"]}," to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Johannesburg"]]}," and ",{"type":"'''","value":["east"]}," to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Durban"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Pietermaritzburg"]]},".\n\nThe train station is in the city centre, on the corner of Maitland and Harvey streets.\n\nFor train ticket bookings, phone 086 000 8888 (from within SA) or +27 (0)11 774 4555 (from outside SA).\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By car"]},"\nThe ",{"type":"'''","value":["N1"]},", ",{"type":"'''","value":["N6"]}," and ",{"type":"'''","value":["N8"]}," national highways meet in Bloemfontein, making it easily reachable from any part of the country.\n\nThe ",{"type":"'''","value":["N1"]}," northbound from Bloemfontein towards ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Gauteng"]]}," is a toll road.\n\n",{"type":"====","value":["Distances"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" Bloemfontein-",{"type":"[[","value":[["Johannesburg"]]},": 398 km"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Bloemfontein-",{"type":"[[","value":[["Cape Town"]]},": 1004 km"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Bloemfontein-",{"type":"[[","value":[["Maseru"]]},": 137 km"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Bloemfontein-",{"type":"[[","value":[["Port Elizabeth"]]},": 677 km"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Bloemfontein-",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kimberley (South Africa)"],["Kimberley"]]},": 160 km"]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By bus"]},"\nA number of bus services offer connections to major South African cities.\n",{"type":"*","value":["  ",{"type":"{{","value":[["listing"],["name=Greyhound"],["url=http:\/\/www.greyhound.