in the sculpture garden at the back and is the ideal retreat from the city's sterile shopping malls."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Women's Memorial"],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Presidency Museum"],["url="],["email="],["address=Pres. Brand Street"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+27 (0)51 448-0949"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours=Open 10AM-12:15PM and 1PM-4PM Tuesday to Friday"],["price="],["content=This former residence of presidents of the Orange Free Stare Republic has been restored to what it would have been at the turn of the century."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Queens Fort Military Museum"],["url="],["email=naln@majuba.ofs.gov.za"],["address=116 Church Street"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+27 (0)51 447-5478"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours=Open 10AM-12:15PM and 1PM-4PM Monday to Friday"],["price="],["content=Exhibitions on the two ",{"type":"''","value":["Boer"]}," wars and the apartheid struggle."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=SA Armour Museum"],["url=http:\/\/newsite.ipmssa.za.org\/content\/view\/248\/68\/"],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions=West of town, follow Nelson Mandela (R64) west towards the N1, you'll see a sign"],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=The SA Armour Museum, on the grounds of Tempe Military Base, exhibits various items dealing specifically with military armour. The SA Armour Museum consists of an indoor-, outdoor-, and reference library area. Some of the more interesting exhibits include South African built apartheid era riot control vehicles, and some old Soviet tanks the South African's captured in Angola."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=First Car Rental"],["alt=First Car Rental : Affordable car hire in South Africa"],["url=http:\/\/www.firstcarrental.co.za\/-Free-State.aspx"],["email="],["address=Bloemfontein Airport"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+27 (0)51 433-2146"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours=07AM-5PM"],["price="],["content=First Car Rental offers great car hire deals in the Free State and the rest of South Africa. Our locations in the Free State include Bloemfontein airport and Bloemfontein downtown."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" Go to the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Waterfront"]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" Play a round of ",{"type":"'''","value":["golf"]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" Visit one of the numerous ",{"type":"'''","value":["game reserves"]}," in the area and go sightseeing \/ hunting"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Take a walk through the tree-lined ",{"type":"'''","value":["President Brand Street"]}," and visit the various ",{"type":"'''","value":["museums"]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" Take a drive through the ",{"type":"'''","value":["northern suburbs"]}," and see the lush gardens"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Visit the ",{"type":"'''","value":["City Zoo"]}," just behind the Waterfront shopping mall.  This zoo is home to a stuffed ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Liger Liger"]}," a cross between a lion and a tiger, that was bred at the zoo in the 1930s. This specimen holds the world record for being the largest ever living cat. And at 798 kg you can see why!"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["do"],["name=Soetdoring Nature Reserve"],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions=about 40 km from Bloemfontein on the main Bultfontein road"],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours=closes at 18.00"],["price=R20 per car"],["content=A pleasant Free State nature reserve close to Bloemfontein. What sets\nit apart are the lions in the small enclosure in the middle of the park – although the enclosure is big enough to mean that you are not\nguaranteed to see the cats. The rest of the reserve is pleasant with open plains, wooded areas and a dam – there are no dangerous animals in the main park so walking is allowed. There is a one-day hiking trail which follow the Modder River, easy enough for families with young children."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Learn"]},"\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["listing"],["name=University of the Free State"],["url=http:\/\/www.ufs.ac.za"],["email=niemannaja@ufs.ac.za"],["address=Bloemfontein"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+27 (0)51 401-3219"],["tollfree="],["fax=+27 (0)51 401-9185"],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["listing"],["name=Central University of Technology (CUT)"],["url=http:\/\/www.cut.ac.za"],["email=mmoss@cut.ac.za"],["address=Bloemfontein"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+27 (0)51 507-3911"],["tollfree="],["fax=+27 (0)51 507-3199"],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Work"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Buy"]},"\nThe ongoing expansion of the Waterfront mall means that Bloemfontein now has two branches of each of the standard South African chain stores (the other branches being in the Mimosa Mall 2 km up the road).  There is a craft market near the Waterfront mall on the first Saturday of the month. Many shops close Saturday afternoons and all day Sunday.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\nPeople eat ",{"type":"''","value":["early"]}," in Bloemfontein - even by South African standards, if you arrive at a restaurant after 7:30PM, especially on a weeknight, you may get some funny looks from the staff, and rushed service as they try to get you out the door so they can lock up and go home.\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=Fishpaste restaurant and bar"],["url="],["email="],["address=31 President Steyn ave, Westdene"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+27 (0)51 430-2662"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content= The place to go. Excellent food in an interesting atmosphere."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=Mexican Restaurant"],["url="],["email="],["address=19A Second Avenue Westdene"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=051 4304526"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=There isn't much that is Mexican about this place, except for the big Aztec statue that overlooks the dining area. Seafood and Steakhouse. One of the city's more upmarket steakhouses. Fantastic food and service in a beautiful restaurant with a selective bar .Winner of numerous awards for food and service.Come and enjoy!"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=Cape Town Fish Market"],["url=http:\/\/www.ctfm.co.za\/location\/index1.php?province=55"],["email="],["address=Eeufees Road"],["lat=-29.08806"],["long=26.21279"],["directions=Northridge mall"],["phone=051 436 6148"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Branch of the popular CTFM chain. Worth the trip into the northern suburbs."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=Beethoven's Cafe Restaurant"],["url="],["email="],["address=Victorian Square, Second Avenue"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=051 448 7223"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=A good choice for breakfast, lunch or a light dinner, and a tad more sophisticated (by Bloemfontein standards) than the chain restaurants in the shopping malls. The only downside is that the terrace overlooks the car park."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=New York's"],["url="],["email="],["address=60 Medene Centre, Second Ave"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=051 447-7279"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=One of the better steakhouses in town, although not the best. Not a bad choice for families."]]}]},